__git_head_message__ = '================================================================================\n\nHost Power Tools / HIP-708\nUser cannot run volume list, ugly message appears\n\nType:              Bug                               Status:        Open                       Assignee: Arnon Yaari\nPriority:          Minor                             Resolution:    Unresolved                 Reporter: Leon Kull\nAffects Version/s:                                   Fix Version/s: 1.1.2\nComponents:                                                                                    Created: 2013-08-20 16:59\nLabels:                                                                                        Updated: 2013-09-01 11:35\n\nIssue Links:\n\nSub-Tasks:\n\nDescription:\nUser DTMLLUAdminUser (it\'s admin account) cannot use HIP and get this message :\nPlease change to something more user-friendly.\n\n{noformat}\nC:\\Users\\DTMLLUAdminUser.HCK2012-2>\nPS C:\\Users\\DTMLLUAdminUser> infinihost volume list\ncan\'t open file \'C:\\PROGRA~1\\INFINI~1\\HOSTPO~1\\bin\\INFINI~1-script.py\' [Errno 2] No such file or directory\n{noformat}\n\nLater :\n\n{noformat}\nC:\\Users\\DTMLLUAdminUser.HCK2012-2>infinihost system list\nSerial   System Name                 Host Name                   System Version\n20000    ibox517                     hck2012-2                   1.3.0\n\nC:\\Users\\DTMLLUAdminUser.HCK2012-2>infinihost connectivity list\nPort Model     State     WWN                 Remote WWNs\nQLE2562        online    21000024ff366231    5742b0f0004e2031\n                                             5742b0f0004e2022\n                                             5742b0f0004e2012\nQLE2562        online    21000024ff366230    5742b0f0004e2031\n                                             5742b0f0004e2022\n                                             5742b0f0004e2012\n\nC:\\Users\\DTMLLUAdminUser.HCK2012-2>infinihost volume list\nCaught an unhandled exception\nLog file is located at C:\\Users\\DTMLLU~1.HCK\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\infinihost.2013-\n08-26.16-43-1.debug.log\n{noformat}\n\nComments:\nGuy Rozendorn added a comment - 2013-08-20 17:08\nnon-admin users cannot run infinihost volume list, but thats not the problem in this case -- it doesn\'t find the python files.\nwhere are you running this from?\n\nGuy Rozendorn added a comment - 2013-08-20 19:16\nmessed up user\n\nLeon Kull added a comment - 2013-08-27 11:24\nThis may reveal a bug.\nCurrently the command "infinihost" spawns a separate CMD window on hck2012-1\nI want to Reopen this ticket.\n\nArnon Yaari added a comment - 2013-08-29 18:08\nWe need to remove the manifest code that requires elevated privileges, and make ensure_root work for real Admin only\n\nGuy Rozendorn added a comment - 2013-08-29 18:09\n[http://www.davidmoore.info/2011/06/20/how-to-check-if-the-current-user-is-an-administrator-even-if-uac-is-on/]\n[http://blogs.msdn.com/b/cjacks/archive/2006/10/09/how-to-determine-if-a-user-is-a-member-of-the-administrators-group-with-uac-enabled-on-windows-vista.aspx]\n\nArnon Yaari added a comment - 2013-08-29 18:18\nI\'m not sure TokenElevationType is the correct class to check, I think it should be TokenIntegrityLevel - the integrity level of the process must be high:\nhttp://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb625966.aspx\nand we must change IsUserAnAdmin to use the lower-level function because it is deprecated:\nhttp://www.cplusplus.com/forum/windows/86818/'
